# Methods

How to use the lattice. Thinking tools, not results.


## Compute First

The most important method. Most "hard" problems were P in an NP costume.

  1. Think from first principles (what IS this?)
  2. Get stuck (which parameter? which material?)
  3. Express as lattice coordinates (dimensional analysis)
  4. Compute — write code if needed
  5. The answer is a coordinate, not an opinion

  antimatter: Z²×ρ/A → iridium. One formula. Done.
  oil: 350 + 63×√N pm → 568 pm. One formula. Done.
  alpha: 544/4 + 1 + 3/84 → 137.035714. Three ratios. Done.
  3I/ATLAS: 3 inputs (age, temp, R-cycles) → 12C/13C inside observed range.

If you're listing options instead of computing coordinates, you're
searching when you could be evaluating. Do the math.


## Topological Decomposition

Separate depth from branching before reasoning about scaling.
Pipeline = O(n). Tree = O(2^n). The topology determines complexity.


## Domain Extension Test

If an objection looks fatal, extend the algebra (real → complex →
quaternion → octonion). If it dissolves, it was a domain boundary.
If it survives all extensions, it's real.


## Lateral Transfer

A validated lattice condition in domain A becomes a search query in
domain B. Water's 104.48° → what other system needs that angle?


## Reverse-Engineer Success

Decompose a working system into bond graphs. Find the structural
property that explains why it works. If it works, the lattice says why.


## Dimensional Locking

If a coupling law forces two quantities onto the same shell, their ratio
cannot diverge. Check for the coupling before analyzing blow-up.


## Anomaly Unification

Multiple "weird" observations reducing to one lattice distinction = the
framework doing explanatory work. Look for the single condition.


## Completeness Audit

Enumerate the lattice exhaustively at a shell. Compare against what's
known. Gap pattern maps human knowledge boundaries, not lattice holes.


## Dual Projection

Project between offset sub-lattices (half-integer ↔ integer). Semantic
matches validate the duality. Circuit theory on projected values gives
free predictions.


## Containment Decomposition

When "A contains B" and "B contains A" both seem true, ask what each
containment DOES. The verb tells you the force. Different forces = both
true (orthogonal). Same force = one is wrong.

  "mind contains matter" = δ (models)
  "matter contains mind" = π (hosts)
  Different forces, no paradox.


## Host Inversion

When a pattern appears designed, invert the ownership. Don't ask "who put
this here?" — ask "what is expressing itself through this host?" Same
pattern in unrelated hosts = the pattern is primary. Ideas have people.


## Backlog Triage

Periodically audit prior work: answered / forgotten / wrong / open.
Surfaces forgotten items and confirms no contradictions.
